B E L I E V E 🦋

2 years ago, I started blogging. Deep inside my heart, I knew it was time to make the magic happen! And today when I look back, I feel so grateful to live my passion and a life I am proud of. It's a beautiful feeling to listen to your heart and do what makes your soul happy despite of all the odds🥰 With hardwork, patience and consistency, I've been my true self always. Hectic schedules, last minute shoots, teamwork, dealing with brands, infinite outfit changes and what not! I've learned to embrace my journey in all It's ups and downs. Afterall, diamonds are made under pressure💎 

I am blessed beyond measure to have my family, friends, my team who have always supported me. My lovely Insta fam, I am thankful to each one of you for the insane amount of love you show here. It always makes my day and keeps me going💕🌻

CHEERS TO THIS BEAUTIFUL, CRAZY JOURNEY OF TWO YEARS🌟🎀🌈 Way to go!
I'll keep up my spirit, always. 

Also, to anyone who is willing to start their journey, take the first step and when you'll back, all you'll see is magic. The magic is in you, believe❤️

Prevention isn’t a trend, it’s a choice. HPV vaccination can help prevent cervical cancer and other certain HPV-related cancers. Just like any other vaccine, HPV 
vaccine might cause mild side effects, such as a slight fever or some pain at the injection site which are temporary. 

Consult your gynaecologist. Every woman deserves to know. 

Please remember, this information is intended for awareness only. For personalized advice and more details on HPV prevention, consult your gynaecologist. This message is issued in public interest by MSD Pharmaceuticals.
